1
00:01:27,410 --> 00:01:31,880
[The Dark Romance]

2
00:01:32,150 --> 00:01:34,900
[Episode 2]

3
00:01:35,310 --> 00:01:36,229
Hello, Xia Yi?

4
00:01:36,680 --> 00:01:37,479
It's Yan Ling.

5
00:01:39,280 --> 00:01:40,140
Did you know...

6
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:42,200
that Leilei had a tattoo?

7
00:01:43,509 --> 00:01:45,200
You... just found out?

8
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:46,920
When did she get it?

9
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:49,710
She was very afraid of pain.

10
00:01:49,710 --> 00:01:51,440
She was even afraid of needles.

11
00:01:51,759 --> 00:01:53,490
How could she ever get a tattoo?

12
00:01:53,920 --> 00:01:55,720
The first time we were intimate,

13
00:01:55,870 --> 00:01:56,840
I noticed it.

14
00:01:57,789 --> 00:01:58,840
Having a tattoo

15
00:01:58,840 --> 00:01:59,920
wasn't a big deal,

16
00:02:01,040 --> 00:02:02,700
but I still asked her about it.

17
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:04,590
She said

18
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:07,040
it was just a memento of her past.

19
00:02:07,510 --> 00:02:09,710
But I know everything about her past.

20
00:02:10,520 --> 00:02:12,120
Didn't you just find out

21
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:13,720
that she had a tattoo?

22
00:02:14,840 --> 00:02:17,310
I thought this was her privacy.

23
00:02:18,520 --> 00:02:19,980
She didn't want us to know,

24
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:21,930
and we should respect that.

25
00:02:24,240 --> 00:02:27,100
Just thinking about her
lying in that cold place...

26
00:02:32,910 --> 00:02:33,710
Today...

27
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:37,320
they closed the case as suicide.

28
00:02:38,910 --> 00:02:40,310
Tomorrow morning at 9:30

29
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,400
at Xiaguan Funeral Home.

30
00:02:43,910 --> 00:02:45,040
You'll come, right?

31
00:02:46,190 --> 00:02:46,680
Got it.

32
00:02:47,150 --> 00:02:48,610
I'll definitely be there.

33
00:02:55,940 --> 00:02:57,930
[Ms. Xu, Class 3 (Grade 4)]
[Refuse] [Answer]

34
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:00,490
Hello, Ms. Xu.

35
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:02,870
He stole my little turtle

36
00:03:02,870 --> 00:03:04,030
just to get back at me!

37
00:03:04,030 --> 00:03:05,050
I didn't!

38
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:05,840
Enough!

39
00:03:06,470 --> 00:03:07,750
Last time you hit our Haoyang,

40
00:03:07,750 --> 00:03:08,710
I didn't say anything!

41
00:03:08,710 --> 00:03:10,390
Now you're stealing from us?

42
00:03:10,590 --> 00:03:12,720
You... You have such a vile character!

43
00:03:14,870 --> 00:03:15,870
Did you hit him?

44
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:17,700
Why?

45
00:03:19,710 --> 00:03:21,360
He called me a big liar...

46
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:25,340
and said I even lied about
my godmother's death.

47
00:03:28,470 --> 00:03:30,079
Then my son was right to hit him.

48
00:03:30,079 --> 00:03:31,140
W-What did you say?

49
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:33,680
You're accusing my son, Yan Jiale,
of stealing

50
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:34,280
and lying.

51
00:03:34,590 --> 00:03:36,650
Those are very serious accusations.

52
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:38,240
He didn't lie.

53
00:03:40,190 --> 00:03:42,380
We did just lose...

54
00:03:44,079 --> 00:03:45,610
a very close family member.

55
00:03:48,910 --> 00:03:51,000
Don't think that just because I said
he deserved it,

56
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:53,060
you actually had the right to hit him.

57
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:54,980
Haven't I told you before,

58
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:58,930
only incompetent people resort to violence
to solve problems?

59
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:01,000
I won't play any games today.

60
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,400
I'll do five more pages
of workbook exercises

61
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:04,000
and write a self-criticism.

62
00:04:06,930 --> 00:04:07,660
Hello.

63
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:09,150
I'd like to ask

64
00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:10,750
if a woman

65
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:12,630
had an eye-design tattoo done

66
00:04:11,700 --> 00:04:15,940
[List of Tattoos Shop in Lihai City]

67
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:14,310
at your shop.

68
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:15,680
She was in her 30s.

69
00:04:16,490 --> 00:04:18,149
I've sent you the design.

70
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:20,120
Nobody?

71
00:04:21,630 --> 00:04:22,260
Thank you.

72
00:04:25,320 --> 00:04:28,250
I've finished the workbook
and the self-criticism.

73
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:36,510
Did Godmother do a lot of bad things?

74
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:41,240
Is it true that she stole a lot of money
from others and couldn't pay it back,

75
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:43,370
so she committed suicide out of guilt?

76
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:45,720
Who told you that?

77
00:04:45,820 --> 00:04:47,350
It's all over the internet.

78
00:04:52,159 --> 00:04:53,360
I'm not quite sure...

79
00:04:54,390 --> 00:04:56,720
about the full story
of your godmother yet.

80
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:58,050
When I know everything,

81
00:04:58,310 --> 00:04:59,770
I'll definitely tell you,

82
00:04:59,870 --> 00:05:00,270
okay?

83
00:05:02,280 --> 00:05:04,410
What if she really did some bad things?

84
00:05:17,750 --> 00:05:19,610
I'll go pick up her parents later.

85
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:21,880
You can go directly to the funeral home.

86
00:05:21,930 --> 00:05:23,000
Isn't Jiale going?

87
00:05:24,510 --> 00:05:25,710
Did you even tell him?

88
00:05:26,270 --> 00:05:27,920
I'm afraid he'd be too heartbroken,

89
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:29,050
so I didn't tell him.

90
00:05:29,510 --> 00:05:30,720
Better not let him go.

91
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:31,950
Okay.

92
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:34,100
See you later.

93
00:05:51,830 --> 00:05:52,560
Get up.

94
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:54,890
Come to the living room.

95
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:00,400
Come here.

96
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:06,410
Yan Jiale,

97
00:06:07,310 --> 00:06:09,510
do you know what makes me the most angry?

98
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:11,750
It's not that you took
your classmate's thing

99
00:06:11,750 --> 00:06:12,830
out of curiosity.

100
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:16,010
It's that you've shattered the trust
I had in you!

101
00:06:17,120 --> 00:06:18,120
In a bit, you need to take the turtle

102
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:20,280
back to school and return it
to your classmate.

103
00:06:20,280 --> 00:06:21,810
Apologize properly to him.

104
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:23,650
Then go find Ms. Xu yourself

105
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,330
and admit your mistake.

106
00:06:25,830 --> 00:06:28,310
When you come back tonight,
we'll have a serious talk.

107
00:06:28,310 --> 00:06:29,770
Aren't you coming with me?

108
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:30,900
I'm busy today.

109
00:06:32,270 --> 00:06:33,680
You need to take responsibility

110
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:34,940
for your own mistakes.

111
00:06:55,909 --> 00:06:56,800
Her parents

112
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:58,920
seem to have aged so much overnight.

113
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:01,600
And Xia Yi,

114
00:07:02,510 --> 00:07:03,640
he's quite pitiful.

115
00:07:04,450 --> 00:07:06,210
Be nicer to Jiale these days.

116
00:07:06,470 --> 00:07:08,470
Pay more attention to his feelings.

117
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:10,480
After all, since childhood,

118
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:12,280
he's spent more time with Leilei

119
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:14,000
than with you, hasn't he?

120
00:07:14,120 --> 00:07:15,780
He's not a little kid anymore.

121
00:07:17,080 --> 00:07:20,560
He needs to learn to be reasonable
and to distinguish right from wrong.

122
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:22,290
No one can protect him forever.

123
00:07:22,310 --> 00:07:23,570
He's only 10 years old.

124
00:07:24,950 --> 00:07:25,750
Not everyone is like you,

125
00:07:25,750 --> 00:07:27,810
with such strong mental resilience.

126
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:29,480
If Leilei hadn't told me,

127
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:31,190
I wouldn't even have known I had a son.

128
00:07:31,190 --> 00:07:34,920
I only found out after I asked you—
and he was already over a year old.

129
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:38,950
Ms. Xu.

130
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:40,730
Hello, Jiale's mom.

131
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:42,270
Is Jiale feeling better?

132
00:07:42,270 --> 00:07:44,200
Jiale? What's wrong with him?

133
00:07:44,270 --> 00:07:45,600
Didn't you send me a message this morning

134
00:07:44,570 --> 00:07:46,360
[Ms. Xu, Class 3 (Grade 4)]

135
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:46,560
saying he wasn't feeling well

136
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:47,870
and asking for time off for him?

137
00:07:47,870 --> 00:07:48,680
No, I didn't.

138
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:51,050
I didn't send you a WeChat message.

139
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:52,930
Then where did he go?

140
00:07:52,950 --> 00:07:53,890
He didn't come to school today.

141
00:07:53,890 --> 00:07:55,240
He didn't come to school?

142
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:57,180
I dropped him off at school this morning!

143
00:07:57,180 --> 00:07:58,780
Then, I-I'll hurry home and check.

144
00:07:58,780 --> 00:07:59,440
Okay, okay.

145
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:01,770
Did you two have another fight?

146
00:08:05,240 --> 00:08:05,900
Is he there?

147
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:07,430
He's not at Leilei's place.

148
00:08:07,430 --> 00:08:08,960
He's not at my place either.

149
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:10,040
Jiale!

150
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:12,970
I-I'm sorry.

151
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:14,600
I-I'm sorry.

152
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:15,830
E-Excuse me,

153
00:08:15,830 --> 00:08:16,310
have you...

154
00:08:16,310 --> 00:08:17,710
have you seen this child?

155
00:08:18,430 --> 00:08:19,740
Have you seen this boy?

156
00:08:24,630 --> 00:08:25,520
Zihao's mom,

157
00:08:25,620 --> 00:08:27,630
has Jiale contacted Zihao today?

158
00:08:28,670 --> 00:08:29,430
It's okay, it's okay.

159
00:08:29,430 --> 00:08:30,030
Thank you.

160
00:08:33,270 --> 00:08:34,030
Have something to eat.

161
00:08:34,030 --> 00:08:35,600
Could something have happened to Jiale?

162
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:36,750
Nothing will happen to him!

163
00:08:36,750 --> 00:08:38,280
Don't think that way, okay?

164
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:39,549
He's such a smart kid.

165
00:08:39,549 --> 00:08:41,409
Nothing will happen to him, okay?

166
00:08:42,150 --> 00:08:43,409
Have some water first.

167
00:08:43,669 --> 00:08:44,930
Here, have some water.

168
00:08:47,520 --> 00:08:48,380
Longhui River.

169
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:07,790
How could you... How could you...

170
00:09:07,790 --> 00:09:09,320
How could you run away from home?

171
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:10,510
I've told you before...

172
00:09:10,510 --> 00:09:11,910
you're never allowed to do this,
no matter what!

173
00:09:11,910 --> 00:09:12,670
That's enough. Enough!

174
00:09:12,670 --> 00:09:13,320
We found him, that's what matters!

175
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:14,650
Why are you hitting him?

176
00:09:15,030 --> 00:09:17,440
And you, you nearly scared us to death,
you know that?

177
00:09:17,440 --> 00:09:18,440
Apologize right now.

178
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:20,240
What's the point of apologizing to me?

179
00:09:20,240 --> 00:09:22,740
Stealing, lying, and skipping school—

180
00:09:22,910 --> 00:09:24,080
look at yourself now.

181
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:25,200
What have you become?

182
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,360
No matter what happens in the future,

183
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:27,720
don't ever do this again, understand?

184
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:30,000
You went to Godmother's funeral today,

185
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:30,660
didn't you?

186
00:09:33,510 --> 00:09:36,040
You were wearing black clothes
this morning.

187
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:38,360
Dad is also dressed all in black now.

188
00:09:38,430 --> 00:09:39,380
[With respect, Yan Ling]

189
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:41,970
[Deeply mourning Ms. Jian Leilei]

190
00:09:43,790 --> 00:09:45,240
You both kept it from me!

191
00:09:45,790 --> 00:09:47,200
We kept it from you because...

192
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:49,600
Because you think she was a bad person

193
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:51,740
whose mistakes couldn't be forgiven!

194
00:09:52,100 --> 00:09:54,430
You didn't want me to see her
one last time!

195
00:09:55,270 --> 00:09:55,910
Yan Ling,

196
00:09:56,910 --> 00:09:57,870
I'll leave

197
00:09:58,630 --> 00:09:59,490
the rest to you.

198
00:10:01,840 --> 00:10:03,120
Don't worry, Uncle.

199
00:10:03,530 --> 00:10:04,390
You don't even

200
00:10:04,390 --> 00:10:05,970
care about what I think.

201
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,490
It doesn't even matter.

202
00:10:08,110 --> 00:10:10,150
All you care about is
whether I did the right thing

203
00:10:10,150 --> 00:10:11,520
or made mistakes.

204
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:13,840
So what if I lied,

205
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:15,680
skipped class, or stole things?

206
00:10:15,870 --> 00:10:17,580
This is who I am now!

207
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:20,020
Alright, alright.

208
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:21,540
Alright.

209
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:27,600
Be good.

210
00:10:30,960 --> 00:10:32,960
Get in the car with me. Let's go home.

211
00:10:33,910 --> 00:10:34,480
Yan Ling!

212
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:38,400
Let him stay at my place tonight.

213
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:51,810
Selling the house and car should be enough

214
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:54,030
to cover most of the money

215
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:56,720
Leilei embezzled.

216
00:10:57,320 --> 00:10:57,910
Okay.

217
00:10:58,910 --> 00:11:00,110
In our Jian family,

218
00:11:00,390 --> 00:11:01,630
for generations...

219
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:05,200
no one has ever broken the law.

220
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:09,210
We don't want to go back there anymore.

221
00:11:09,910 --> 00:11:11,310
It's too heartbreaking.

222
00:11:13,630 --> 00:11:16,220
If you can't bear to,
we can keep the baby.

223
00:11:16,750 --> 00:11:18,200
I've passed my probation period,

224
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:19,720
and my salary will go up every year.

225
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:22,020
Don't worry. Just focus on your studies.

226
00:11:28,270 --> 00:11:29,360
I'm here for you.

227
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:30,790
You and I—one birth mother
and one godmother—

228
00:11:30,790 --> 00:11:31,750
are both so capable.

229
00:11:31,750 --> 00:11:33,480
I'm sure we can raise one child,

230
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:34,160
right?

231
00:11:34,870 --> 00:11:36,470
Everything will get better.

232
00:11:36,630 --> 00:11:38,000
It'll all work out fine.

233
00:12:05,790 --> 00:12:06,630
Ms. Yan?

234
00:12:17,560 --> 00:12:18,490
Are you alright?

235
00:12:21,270 --> 00:12:21,990
I'm fine.

236
00:12:26,870 --> 00:12:28,530
Have you had too much to drink?

237
00:12:29,500 --> 00:12:30,900
How about I take you home?

238
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:37,150
I'm fine. I'm doing well.

239
00:12:37,460 --> 00:12:38,660
Don't worry about me.

240
00:12:50,930 --> 00:12:52,510
[8th Anniversary Sale—Shop 'Til You Drop]

241
00:12:53,630 --> 00:12:55,030
I'm fine. I'm doing well.

242
00:12:58,380 --> 00:13:00,370
[8th Anniversary Sale—Shop 'Til You Drop]

243
00:13:25,100 --> 00:13:27,570
♪ It's like a dream ♪

244
00:13:28,300 --> 00:13:31,240
♪ Our encounter was so fleeting ♪

245
00:13:32,510 --> 00:13:33,940
♪ You came like a spring breeze ♪

246
00:13:34,220 --> 00:13:38,750
♪ Softly blowing into my heart ♪

247
00:13:40,070 --> 00:13:46,550
♪ Where has your smile gone? ♪

248
00:13:47,530 --> 00:13:53,290
♪ That familiar smile I remember so well ♪

249
00:13:53,770 --> 00:13:58,410
♪ Do you know that I love you, miss you,
resent you, and long for you? ♪

250
00:13:58,720 --> 00:14:01,080
♪ My love will never change ♪

251
00:14:02,220 --> 00:14:05,910
♪ Have you ever thought about ♪

252
00:14:06,140 --> 00:14:08,990
♪ The vow we once made? ♪

253
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:13,300
♪ Even if you're drawn to the daffodils ♪

254
00:14:13,710 --> 00:14:16,340
♪ Blooming by the water ♪

255
00:14:18,270 --> 00:14:20,470
I wanted to write my thesis properly...

256
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:22,200
But I didn't know what was wrong with me.

257
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:24,260
I just couldn't continue writing...

258
00:14:25,390 --> 00:14:27,410
But... But Feng said

259
00:14:27,430 --> 00:14:28,980
if I couldn't graduate,

260
00:14:29,150 --> 00:14:29,690
I...

261
00:14:29,840 --> 00:14:32,120
I'd be even more unworthy of his family.

262
00:14:32,390 --> 00:14:34,000
If I don't get my diploma,

263
00:14:34,550 --> 00:14:36,590
my dad will kill me.

264
00:14:37,030 --> 00:14:38,730
You can rewrite your thesis.

265
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:40,800
When you're feeling better,

266
00:14:41,150 --> 00:14:42,350
I'll help you with it.

267
00:14:43,270 --> 00:14:44,930
You'll definitely graduate.

268
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:47,310
Don't cry anymore.

269
00:14:47,310 --> 00:14:47,910
It's okay.

270
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:49,860
Actually, it's good to cry it out.

271
00:14:51,520 --> 00:14:53,000
Your mother is getting food
at the cafeteria.

272
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,600
She won't be back right away.

273
00:14:54,730 --> 00:14:56,860
If you want to cry, cry it out properly.

274
00:14:57,870 --> 00:14:58,440
Ms. Yan.

275
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:20,690
Can you help me with something?

276
00:15:22,390 --> 00:15:23,200
What is it?

277
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:25,450
Can you help me contact

278
00:15:25,910 --> 00:15:26,480
Li Changning's boyfriend,

279
00:15:26,480 --> 00:15:27,600
Xu Feng,

280
00:15:28,030 --> 00:15:29,230
through your school?

281
00:15:32,030 --> 00:15:34,050
Come on!

282
00:15:32,060 --> 00:15:33,660
[Lihai University
of Finance and Economics]

283
00:15:42,910 --> 00:15:43,640
Come on!

284
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:53,550
Feng, you're amazing!

285
00:15:53,680 --> 00:15:54,600
Here, you must be tired.

286
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:56,330
Here, have something to drink.

287
00:15:58,430 --> 00:16:00,960
Don't you know I don't drink
such sweet stuff?

288
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:03,060
Pick one, then.

289
00:16:03,270 --> 00:16:04,530
They're all ice-cold.

290
00:16:09,530 --> 00:16:12,270
[Lihai University
of Finance and Economics]

291
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:15,710
Xu Feng!

292
00:16:16,680 --> 00:16:17,500
Xu Feng!

293
00:16:20,840 --> 00:16:21,540
Ms. Wang!

294
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:24,100
I don't know anything.

295
00:16:24,840 --> 00:16:26,720
I've already broken up with Li Changning.

296
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:28,180
If I keep caring about her,

297
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:30,180
my girlfriend will call me a jerk.

298
00:16:31,530 --> 00:16:32,870
After the incident,

299
00:16:32,900 --> 00:16:35,430
we also talked to Xu Feng
about the situation.

300
00:16:35,610 --> 00:16:38,330
It was indeed just a relationship dispute.

301
00:16:38,530 --> 00:16:39,790
We're all very sorry

302
00:16:40,390 --> 00:16:41,550
that this happened.

303
00:16:42,750 --> 00:16:45,010
You were already dating a new girlfriend

304
00:16:45,510 --> 00:16:47,700
while you were still
with Li Changning, right?

305
00:16:47,700 --> 00:16:48,960
What are you implying?

306
00:16:49,150 --> 00:16:50,700
Feng broke up with her ages ago.

307
00:16:50,700 --> 00:16:51,510
She's the shameless one

308
00:16:51,510 --> 00:16:53,120
who kept clinging to Feng. Right?

309
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:53,910
Excuse me, miss,

310
00:16:53,910 --> 00:16:54,870
which department are you from?

311
00:16:54,870 --> 00:16:55,810
I'm not from your school,

312
00:16:55,810 --> 00:16:57,610
so you've got no control over me.

313
00:16:58,190 --> 00:17:00,050
I can see you're very much in love.

314
00:17:00,930 --> 00:17:03,390
Since you believe so deeply in
what you have,

315
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:04,930
could you please tell me

316
00:17:05,730 --> 00:17:07,109
why you snuck into the hospital

317
00:17:07,109 --> 00:17:08,510
in the middle of the night

318
00:17:08,740 --> 00:17:09,869
to see Li Changning?

319
00:17:12,790 --> 00:17:13,609
I didn't.

320
00:17:15,849 --> 00:17:16,680
[Hospital—1st & 2nd Floor Corridor]

321
00:17:18,510 --> 00:17:21,130
[1-2F Corridor, Inpatient Ward]

322
00:17:34,340 --> 00:17:37,590
[1-2F Corridor, Inpatient Ward]

323
00:17:40,770 --> 00:17:41,970
It was you, wasn't it?

324
00:17:52,640 --> 00:17:53,970
Li Changning went crazy

325
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:55,900
and was hospitalized.

326
00:17:56,310 --> 00:17:57,550
What other reason could there be
for my girlfriend

327
00:17:57,550 --> 00:17:59,150
to visit her in the hospital?

328
00:18:01,110 --> 00:18:03,040
Does this really need explaining?

329
00:18:04,640 --> 00:18:06,300
Because she's kind-hearted.

330
00:18:08,640 --> 00:18:09,040
Right?

331
00:18:27,300 --> 00:18:28,790
Li Changning was throwing her life away
for love

332
00:18:28,790 --> 00:18:29,950
and got herself into this state.

333
00:18:29,950 --> 00:18:31,280
It's not worth it at all.

334
00:18:31,590 --> 00:18:32,200
That boy is

335
00:18:32,270 --> 00:18:34,020
clearly just playing with those girls.

336
00:18:34,020 --> 00:18:36,200
But for her, it was a profound love.

337
00:18:36,590 --> 00:18:38,640
Of course, she'd be in pain
after losing it.

338
00:18:38,640 --> 00:18:40,070
No matter how profound the love,

339
00:18:40,070 --> 00:18:41,530
it's not worth destroying yourself.

340
00:18:41,530 --> 00:18:43,720
It only makes the other person
despise you more.

341
00:18:43,720 --> 00:18:44,200
Ms. Yan.

342
00:18:44,960 --> 00:18:46,270
The reason I asked for your help

343
00:18:46,270 --> 00:18:48,400
is not only because you're her teacher

344
00:18:48,480 --> 00:18:50,110
but also because you're both women.

345
00:18:50,110 --> 00:18:51,240
I thought you would understand her better

346
00:18:51,240 --> 00:18:52,150
and empathize with her,

347
00:18:52,150 --> 00:18:54,210
rather than criticize her like this.

348
00:18:56,010 --> 00:18:57,540
You're a privileged woman,

349
00:18:57,750 --> 00:18:59,240
but have you really looked at

350
00:18:59,240 --> 00:19:01,200
what Li Changning's life has been like?

351
00:19:01,200 --> 00:19:03,200
Her parents did send her to college!

352
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:06,530
But you should be able to hear

353
00:19:06,530 --> 00:19:09,130
the reluctance and resentment
in their words.

354
00:19:09,790 --> 00:19:12,510
She was probably overlooked
from the moment she was born.

355
00:19:12,510 --> 00:19:13,680
And after her brother was born,

356
00:19:13,680 --> 00:19:15,350
she was pushed even further
into the background.

357
00:19:15,350 --> 00:19:16,200
Then...

358
00:19:17,070 --> 00:19:19,210
a boy appeared in her life.

359
00:19:19,430 --> 00:19:20,560
He said he loved her.

360
00:19:21,270 --> 00:19:22,480
He told her she was the most

361
00:19:22,480 --> 00:19:23,570
beautiful and important girl

362
00:19:23,570 --> 00:19:25,370
in the world to him.

363
00:19:28,070 --> 00:19:29,830
Do you know what that means

364
00:19:29,850 --> 00:19:30,980
to Li Changning?

365
00:19:33,110 --> 00:19:36,750
If anything, with her childhood trauma
and family misfortunes...

366
00:19:36,750 --> 00:19:40,080
shouldn't she have become
more independent and resilient?

367
00:19:41,560 --> 00:19:43,090
But she's only 20 years old.

368
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:46,000
Even you, Ms. Yan,

369
00:19:46,920 --> 00:19:48,650
haven't you also been drinking

370
00:19:48,750 --> 00:19:50,550
and crying alone in a back alley?

371
00:19:52,160 --> 00:19:53,360
When you were her age,

372
00:19:53,890 --> 00:19:54,590
didn't you ever

373
00:19:54,590 --> 00:19:56,590
lose your mind and go crazy for love?

374
00:19:56,920 --> 00:19:58,980
You don't need to guess about my past.

375
00:19:59,160 --> 00:19:59,960
Rest assured,

376
00:20:00,680 --> 00:20:02,940
my role as her teacher isn't just a title.

377
00:20:03,030 --> 00:20:04,070
She is my student,

378
00:20:04,550 --> 00:20:06,950
and I'll take full responsibility for her.

379
00:20:07,550 --> 00:20:09,160
From now on, you don't need to
concern yourself

380
00:20:09,160 --> 00:20:10,630
with anything besides her treatment.

381
00:20:10,630 --> 00:20:11,000
I...

382
00:20:17,070 --> 00:20:18,670
When you were her age,

383
00:20:18,920 --> 00:20:19,480
didn't you ever

384
00:20:19,480 --> 00:20:21,480
lose your mind and go crazy for love?

385
00:20:24,680 --> 00:20:25,480
Don't! Stop!

386
00:20:25,700 --> 00:20:26,760
Alright, alright.

387
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:28,070
Yan Ling!

388
00:20:38,750 --> 00:20:39,240
Hello?

389
00:20:42,720 --> 00:20:43,310
What?

390
00:20:43,750 --> 00:20:45,480
Back off. Back off.

391
00:20:45,880 --> 00:20:47,640
I'm crazy! I'm not leaving the hospital!

392
00:20:47,640 --> 00:20:49,580
What are you doing?

393
00:20:49,600 --> 00:20:51,720
-Changning, don't be impulsive!
-Back off! Back off!

394
00:20:51,720 --> 00:20:53,270
-She doesn't want me.
-If you make me leave the hospital today,

395
00:20:53,270 --> 00:20:54,720
I'll die right here, believe it or not!

396
00:20:54,720 --> 00:20:56,380
I'll die right in front of you!

397
00:20:57,680 --> 00:20:58,910
No! No!

398
00:20:59,190 --> 00:21:00,310
It's okay! It's okay!

399
00:21:00,310 --> 00:21:02,720
-Mrs. Li, it's fine!
-Shut up! Shut up!

400
00:21:02,830 --> 00:21:03,760
Get out!

401
00:21:03,830 --> 00:21:04,880
Get out!

402
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:07,200
Don't hurt yourself.

403
00:21:07,450 --> 00:21:08,180
Listen to me.

404
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:10,200
I understand you.

405
00:21:10,680 --> 00:21:13,400
It's not that you don't want to
leave the hospital.

406
00:21:13,400 --> 00:21:15,200
You just don't want to leave him.

407
00:21:15,640 --> 00:21:16,090
Right?

408
00:21:18,240 --> 00:21:20,970
If your mother takes you home
after discharge...

409
00:21:22,340 --> 00:21:24,740
you'll never have a chance
to see him again.

410
00:21:26,770 --> 00:21:27,570
Calm down.

411
00:21:29,400 --> 00:21:29,940
Look.

412
00:21:32,960 --> 00:21:34,180
You're an adult now.

413
00:21:34,270 --> 00:21:36,180
If you just sign this form,

414
00:21:36,920 --> 00:21:37,580
your mother

415
00:21:37,720 --> 00:21:39,580
can't make any decisions for you.

416
00:21:40,920 --> 00:21:42,030
I don't believe you.

417
00:21:42,030 --> 00:21:43,480
I don't believe you! Take it away!

418
00:21:43,480 --> 00:21:45,550
Whether you leave the hospital or not
doesn't matter to me.

419
00:21:45,550 --> 00:21:46,160
Trust me.

420
00:21:46,510 --> 00:21:48,040
Just read it and you'll see.

421
00:21:49,370 --> 00:21:50,790
[Test Request Form]

422
00:21:56,480 --> 00:21:57,550
Even Ms. Yan

423
00:21:57,720 --> 00:21:58,520
and the school

424
00:21:58,960 --> 00:21:59,790
cannot

425
00:21:59,790 --> 00:22:01,920
make any discharge decisions for you.

426
00:22:03,480 --> 00:22:05,010
You'll know once you see it.

427
00:22:10,960 --> 00:22:13,140
Whether to leave the hospital or not...

428
00:22:13,140 --> 00:22:14,540
it'll be your own choice.

429
00:22:27,720 --> 00:22:28,550
Grab her. Grab her.

430
00:22:28,550 --> 00:22:31,190
You lied to me! You all lied to me!

431
00:22:31,230 --> 00:22:31,920
Why?

432
00:22:31,920 --> 00:22:33,070
Changning, calm down.

433
00:22:33,070 --> 00:22:33,660
Gently, gently.

434
00:22:33,660 --> 00:22:34,410
Be gentle.

435
00:22:35,480 --> 00:22:36,880
It's alright. It's alright.

436
00:22:36,880 --> 00:22:38,340
Changning, it's alright.

437
00:22:41,310 --> 00:22:42,910
It's alright. It's alright.

438
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:44,840
Prepare the bed. Come on.

439
00:22:44,840 --> 00:22:45,640
It's fine now.

440
00:22:47,440 --> 00:22:48,270
Ms. Yan.

441
00:22:49,550 --> 00:22:50,890
Please tell me

442
00:22:51,270 --> 00:22:53,370
which boy it is.

443
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:55,510
I'll beg him to leave my daughter alone.

444
00:22:55,510 --> 00:22:56,030
Ms. Yan.

445
00:22:56,680 --> 00:22:57,410
Thank you.

446
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:05,810
Ma'am.

447
00:23:06,830 --> 00:23:08,690
You've been here for so many days.

448
00:23:09,270 --> 00:23:11,730
Has that boy ever come to
visit Li Changning?

449
00:23:12,640 --> 00:23:13,400
Do you think

450
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:16,840
the one who won't let go
is him or Changning?

451
00:23:20,920 --> 00:23:22,450
Could you please promise me

452
00:23:23,510 --> 00:23:24,400
that you'll stop reminding her

453
00:23:24,400 --> 00:23:26,440
how much money the family spent on her,

454
00:23:26,440 --> 00:23:28,590
or that she has a brother to worry about?

455
00:23:28,590 --> 00:23:30,110
Just treat her

456
00:23:30,110 --> 00:23:31,770
as if she were your only child.

457
00:23:32,590 --> 00:23:34,650
Care about whether she's eating well

458
00:23:34,720 --> 00:23:35,720
or sleeping well.

459
00:23:36,550 --> 00:23:38,550
Even if it's just for these few days.

460
00:23:41,790 --> 00:23:42,830
But this child...

461
00:23:42,830 --> 00:23:44,400
You saw what she's like.

462
00:23:44,510 --> 00:23:45,970
Now, she's basically like

463
00:23:46,310 --> 00:23:48,910
someone who's taken a bad fall
and gotten hurt.

464
00:23:49,480 --> 00:23:50,920
Let's not blame her

465
00:23:50,920 --> 00:23:52,440
for not watching her step.

466
00:23:53,270 --> 00:23:54,410
Actually, she

467
00:23:54,830 --> 00:23:57,030
didn't want to fall and get hurt either,

468
00:23:57,310 --> 00:23:57,880
did she?

469
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:01,620
Ma'am,

470
00:24:02,270 --> 00:24:04,130
please give me a little more time,

471
00:24:05,200 --> 00:24:07,530
and give Changning a little more time too.

472
00:24:09,310 --> 00:24:09,770
Then...

473
00:24:10,310 --> 00:24:12,400
that paper you just showed her—

474
00:24:12,400 --> 00:24:14,460
you absolutely can't let her sign it.

475
00:24:14,790 --> 00:24:16,270
She's too young and inexperienced.

476
00:24:16,270 --> 00:24:17,310
You mean this?

477
00:24:17,400 --> 00:24:17,870
Yes.

478
00:24:19,240 --> 00:24:20,110
This is fake.

479
00:24:20,110 --> 00:24:21,270
I was just tricking her.

480
00:24:21,270 --> 00:24:22,530
There's no such thing.

481
00:24:29,120 --> 00:24:32,270
Good thing you were here
when that patient lost control today.

482
00:24:32,270 --> 00:24:33,400
What's really going on with her?

483
00:24:33,400 --> 00:24:35,240
She's been here for days
and hasn't gotten any better.

484
00:24:35,240 --> 00:24:37,530
Just be patient
and treat the symptoms accordingly.

485
00:24:37,530 --> 00:24:38,390
Dr. Luo?

486
00:24:39,410 --> 00:24:40,060
Ms. Yan?

487
00:24:41,110 --> 00:24:41,960
I'll be going now.

488
00:24:41,960 --> 00:24:42,490
Bye-bye.

489
00:24:43,720 --> 00:24:45,180
You're... waiting for me?

490
00:24:45,790 --> 00:24:46,560
Dr. Luo.

491
00:24:47,240 --> 00:24:49,030
I'm really glad you were here today.

492
00:24:49,030 --> 00:24:49,720
Otherwise,

493
00:24:49,750 --> 00:24:51,750
who knows what might have happened?

494
00:24:51,880 --> 00:24:52,940
No need to thank me.

495
00:24:53,270 --> 00:24:54,520
About last time,

496
00:24:55,200 --> 00:24:57,070
I couldn't control my emotions.

497
00:24:57,720 --> 00:24:59,320
I wanted to apologize to you.

498
00:25:00,920 --> 00:25:01,640
Last time?

499
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:04,260
Yesterday, after we met with Xu Feng.

500
00:25:06,880 --> 00:25:07,940
I was just kidding.

501
00:25:08,020 --> 00:25:09,280
Actually, I remember.

502
00:25:09,790 --> 00:25:11,850
I suddenly lost composure yesterday

503
00:25:11,960 --> 00:25:13,860
because, indeed, you'd seen me

504
00:25:14,350 --> 00:25:16,040
in such a terrible state

505
00:25:16,550 --> 00:25:17,420
that night.

506
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:20,000
And then, hearing you mention it...

507
00:25:20,650 --> 00:25:22,270
I felt quite embarrassed.

508
00:25:23,070 --> 00:25:24,840
Actually, you don't need to
be embarrassed.

509
00:25:24,840 --> 00:25:26,640
Sometimes losing control is...

510
00:25:28,110 --> 00:25:29,570
a good defense mechanism.

511
00:25:29,590 --> 00:25:30,550
Being able to lose control means

512
00:25:30,550 --> 00:25:32,550
you feel safe in your surroundings.

513
00:25:32,590 --> 00:25:33,920
From that perspective,

514
00:25:35,070 --> 00:25:35,910
I'm honored

515
00:25:36,230 --> 00:25:37,630
that I make you feel safe.

516
00:25:41,590 --> 00:25:42,370
Dr. Luo,

517
00:25:42,830 --> 00:25:45,630
my son and I have been having
some problems lately.

518
00:25:46,160 --> 00:25:47,890
I'd like to ask for your advice.

519
00:25:49,000 --> 00:25:49,660
No problem.

520
00:26:13,300 --> 00:26:15,830
What kind of small animal
are you looking for?

521
00:26:15,880 --> 00:26:16,610
Just browsing.

522
00:26:16,230 --> 00:26:18,480
[Cute Pets Club]

523
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:17,370
Okay.

524
00:26:23,240 --> 00:26:24,960
This one is a new arrival.

525
00:26:24,960 --> 00:26:26,000
It's called the Snowball Hamster.

526
00:26:26,000 --> 00:26:26,960
Very rare.

527
00:26:28,160 --> 00:26:29,590
Can you take it out
so I can see it better?

528
00:26:29,590 --> 00:26:31,190
It's actually quite fierce.

529
00:26:34,800 --> 00:26:36,130
I'll take this one then.

530
00:26:36,400 --> 00:26:37,880
I like ones with character.

531
00:26:37,880 --> 00:26:38,410
Alright.

532
00:27:05,340 --> 00:27:06,400
What are you doing?

533
00:27:07,830 --> 00:27:09,030
Getting some snacks.

534
00:27:10,310 --> 00:27:11,640
Perfect timing, Jiale!

535
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:12,880
Come here. Stop doing homework.

536
00:27:12,880 --> 00:27:14,000
Watch the movie with us.

537
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:15,060
This is super good.

538
00:27:15,850 --> 00:27:18,380
Kids will have nightmares
if they watch this.

539
00:27:18,400 --> 00:27:19,460
You want some cola?

540
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:20,900
I'll just drink half of it.

541
00:27:20,900 --> 00:27:21,920
If you like it, drink it all.

542
00:27:21,920 --> 00:27:23,240
I'll buy you more tomorrow.

543
00:27:23,240 --> 00:27:25,700
Drinking too much of it
is bad for your teeth.

544
00:27:26,230 --> 00:27:28,360
Is that something a kid would say?

545
00:27:28,510 --> 00:27:30,680
You're even more old-fashioned
than your dad...

546
00:27:30,680 --> 00:27:33,010
even more mature and steady than your dad.

547
00:27:33,750 --> 00:27:34,830
I'm going back to do my homework.

548
00:27:34,830 --> 00:27:35,720
Still doing homework?

549
00:27:35,720 --> 00:27:37,830
You've been at it for two hours
and are still not finished?

550
00:27:37,830 --> 00:27:39,360
The school is way too crazy.

551
00:27:39,590 --> 00:27:40,390
That's not it.

552
00:27:40,440 --> 00:27:42,440
His mom has assigned him workbooks.

553
00:27:42,510 --> 00:27:43,000
Coming.

554
00:27:45,360 --> 00:27:46,000
I'm sorry.

555
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:47,590
I didn't tell you in advance.

556
00:27:47,590 --> 00:27:48,490
Jiale.

557
00:27:49,110 --> 00:27:50,970
I wanted to give Jiale a surprise.

558
00:27:51,030 --> 00:27:51,680
Um...

559
00:27:54,400 --> 00:27:55,200
Is this a bad time?

560
00:27:55,200 --> 00:27:56,030
No, no, not at all.

561
00:27:56,030 --> 00:27:58,060
Well, l-let me introduce you...

562
00:27:59,590 --> 00:28:01,440
Hello, I'm Lu's girlfriend.

563
00:28:01,440 --> 00:28:02,570
My name is Fang Fang.

564
00:28:03,720 --> 00:28:04,510
Nice to meet you.

565
00:28:04,510 --> 00:28:05,710
I'm Jiale's mother.

566
00:28:06,350 --> 00:28:06,920
I know.

567
00:28:06,980 --> 00:28:08,480
Jiale was just talking about you.

568
00:28:08,480 --> 00:28:08,910
Right?

569
00:28:08,960 --> 00:28:09,690
No, I wasn't!

570
00:28:09,880 --> 00:28:10,940
Don't be like that.

571
00:28:11,270 --> 00:28:12,310
Well, look at you.

572
00:28:12,310 --> 00:28:13,310
I asked you to grab me a cola.

573
00:28:13,310 --> 00:28:14,370
It took you so long.

574
00:28:14,550 --> 00:28:15,310
This... I...

575
00:28:15,440 --> 00:28:15,920
I want to drink it.

576
00:28:15,920 --> 00:28:16,720
It's fine.

577
00:28:17,590 --> 00:28:19,440
Actually, having a few sips
of cola occasionally

578
00:28:19,440 --> 00:28:20,240
is no big deal.

579
00:28:23,920 --> 00:28:24,660
Jiale,

580
00:28:25,480 --> 00:28:26,740
come home with Mom.

581
00:28:27,790 --> 00:28:28,600
Why go home?

582
00:28:29,830 --> 00:28:31,960
It's not convenient for you
to stay here all the time.

583
00:28:31,960 --> 00:28:33,290
It's quite convenient.

584
00:28:33,590 --> 00:28:34,920
And I have someone to play with.

585
00:28:34,920 --> 00:28:37,050
Alright, alright, I'll play with you.

586
00:28:44,440 --> 00:28:45,940
Come home with me.

587
00:28:46,350 --> 00:28:48,350
I want to have a good talk with you.

588
00:28:49,070 --> 00:28:50,670
Why should I go home with you?

589
00:28:50,850 --> 00:28:52,380
You just want to lecture me!

590
00:28:52,480 --> 00:28:53,550
Have a talk with me?

591
00:28:53,550 --> 00:28:55,150
I don't want to talk with you!

592
00:28:55,680 --> 00:28:57,050
That's not what I meant.

593
00:28:57,160 --> 00:28:57,780
Jiale!

594
00:28:58,420 --> 00:29:00,590
I just want to have
a proper talk with you, Jiale!

595
00:29:00,590 --> 00:29:01,310
Yan Jiale,

596
00:29:01,310 --> 00:29:02,970
what kind of attitude is that?

597
00:29:04,510 --> 00:29:06,470
Kids are just like that.

598
00:29:06,590 --> 00:29:08,160
W-Why don't you come in
and sit for a while?

599
00:29:08,160 --> 00:29:09,560
Wait until he calms down.

600
00:29:10,640 --> 00:29:12,480
How about we let him cool off first

601
00:29:12,480 --> 00:29:14,010
and talk about it tomorrow?

602
00:29:18,720 --> 00:29:19,830
I'll be going then.

603
00:29:20,270 --> 00:29:20,820
Okay.

604
00:29:23,310 --> 00:29:24,070
Don't worry.

605
00:29:24,070 --> 00:29:25,070
He's fine with me.

606
00:29:35,720 --> 00:29:36,680
I told my colleagues

607
00:29:36,680 --> 00:29:38,200
that my son is already in fourth grade,

608
00:29:38,200 --> 00:29:38,830
and they thought

609
00:29:38,830 --> 00:29:41,350
I was lying just to get employee benefits.

610
00:29:41,550 --> 00:29:42,830
So we can really go see

611
00:29:42,830 --> 00:29:44,430
the premiere of Spider-Man?

612
00:29:44,960 --> 00:29:45,910
Of course.

613
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:47,960
I even got you two

614
00:29:47,960 --> 00:29:49,030
autographed posters.

615
00:29:49,030 --> 00:29:49,720
Jiale,

616
00:29:49,960 --> 00:29:51,030
when I get married,

617
00:29:51,030 --> 00:29:52,030
you'll be my flower boy,

618
00:29:52,030 --> 00:29:52,770
okay?

619
00:29:53,270 --> 00:29:54,900
Godmother, you're the best!

620
00:29:56,160 --> 00:29:58,670
You're my guardian angel.

621
00:30:07,440 --> 00:30:08,240
You don't even

622
00:30:08,240 --> 00:30:09,900
care about what I think.

623
00:30:09,960 --> 00:30:11,370
It doesn't even matter.

624
00:30:11,960 --> 00:30:12,720
All you care about is

625
00:30:12,720 --> 00:30:14,000
whether I did the right thing

626
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:15,300
or made mistakes.

627
00:30:15,550 --> 00:30:17,080
You just want to lecture me!

628
00:30:17,110 --> 00:30:18,710
I don't want to talk with you!

629
00:30:39,180 --> 00:30:41,830
[Dr. Luo Liang]

630
00:30:40,720 --> 00:30:41,530
How did it go?

631
00:30:41,680 --> 00:30:43,480
Did your talk with Jiale go well?

632
00:30:47,640 --> 00:30:49,100
Not as well as I expected.

633
00:30:54,240 --> 00:30:55,400
Patience is key.

634
00:30:59,260 --> 00:31:00,130
Okay.

635
00:31:05,000 --> 00:31:06,100
[How did it go?
Did your talk with Jiale go well?]

636
00:31:06,120 --> 00:31:07,270
[Not as well as I expected.]

637
00:31:07,290 --> 00:31:08,280
[Patience is key.]

638
00:31:08,310 --> 00:31:09,530
[Okay.]

639
00:31:20,400 --> 00:31:22,000
They say when a child is sick,

640
00:31:22,070 --> 00:31:24,470
they turn to the person
they're closest to.

641
00:31:25,160 --> 00:31:26,640
When Jiale was sick before,

642
00:31:26,640 --> 00:31:28,240
he always looked for Leilei.

643
00:31:28,350 --> 00:31:29,550
He never came to me.

644
00:31:32,070 --> 00:31:33,470
Today, it suddenly hit me

645
00:31:34,830 --> 00:31:36,700
that I'm not really a good mother.

646
00:31:44,790 --> 00:31:47,000
[Typing...]

647
00:31:55,250 --> 00:31:58,980
[Integrity in Character,
Diligence in Study]

648
00:31:55,550 --> 00:31:57,640
Now, the cause and course
of Li Changning's current condition

649
00:31:57,640 --> 00:31:58,720
are very clear.

650
00:31:59,280 --> 00:32:01,620
It was entirely due to emotional issues.

651
00:32:02,120 --> 00:32:03,760
Her frequent absences,

652
00:32:04,030 --> 00:32:05,200
late assignment submissions,

653
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:07,520
and thesis plagiarism are all confirmed.

654
00:32:07,520 --> 00:32:10,110
Ms. Yan's decision to bar her
from the thesis defense

655
00:32:10,110 --> 00:32:13,160
was entirely in accordance with
regulations and procedures.

656
00:32:13,160 --> 00:32:14,890
There's nothing wrong with it.

657
00:32:15,310 --> 00:32:17,710
This matter has caused
quite a public stir.

658
00:32:18,070 --> 00:32:19,920
Since the matter has been
thoroughly investigated,

659
00:32:19,920 --> 00:32:22,720
we should issue an official statement
as soon as possible

660
00:32:22,720 --> 00:32:24,790
to address public opinion.

661
00:32:26,270 --> 00:32:28,870
We will be completely honest
in our statement.

662
00:32:29,200 --> 00:32:30,590
Regardless of which media outlets
contact us,

663
00:32:30,590 --> 00:32:31,350
we can

664
00:32:31,350 --> 00:32:32,470
clearly

665
00:32:32,470 --> 00:32:34,590
present the facts
and explain the whole thing.

666
00:32:34,590 --> 00:32:35,070
Good.

667
00:32:35,720 --> 00:32:36,370
Once it's finished,

668
00:32:36,370 --> 00:32:37,640
submit it to
the Administrative Office promptly.

669
00:32:37,640 --> 00:32:38,170
Alright.

670
00:32:39,550 --> 00:32:40,410
President Sun,

671
00:32:41,200 --> 00:32:42,730
I have a different opinion.

672
00:32:47,400 --> 00:32:48,310
This child...

673
00:32:48,880 --> 00:32:50,590
Her emotions have been
very unstable lately.

674
00:32:50,590 --> 00:32:53,990
A few days ago, she almost hurt
herself again in the hospital.

675
00:32:54,200 --> 00:32:55,530
She's only 21 years old.

676
00:32:56,350 --> 00:32:57,960
If she has to live the rest of her life

677
00:32:57,960 --> 00:33:00,220
under the stigma of plagiarism,

678
00:33:00,680 --> 00:33:03,030
and if we also disclose
that she had a breakdown

679
00:33:03,030 --> 00:33:04,760
due to relationship problems,

680
00:33:05,070 --> 00:33:06,430
it would be devastating

681
00:33:07,240 --> 00:33:08,720
for someone so young.

682
00:33:09,070 --> 00:33:10,400
That would be too cruel.

683
00:33:11,160 --> 00:33:11,960
Then, Ms. Yan,

684
00:33:12,510 --> 00:33:14,640
how do you think we should handle this?

685
00:33:14,640 --> 00:33:16,300
How about in the statement...

686
00:33:17,750 --> 00:33:19,150
we say that it was my fault

687
00:33:19,590 --> 00:33:20,230
for

688
00:33:20,550 --> 00:33:22,750
not supervising the student properly?

689
00:33:25,680 --> 00:33:26,250
Ms. Yan,

690
00:33:26,550 --> 00:33:28,010
you want to take the blame?

691
00:33:28,400 --> 00:33:29,200
Yes, Ms. Yan.

692
00:33:29,710 --> 00:33:34,150
[Integrity in Character,
Diligence in Study]

693
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:31,070
If the statement is
really written that way,

694
00:33:31,070 --> 00:33:32,670
the school will have to

695
00:33:32,920 --> 00:33:34,680
take disciplinary action against you.

696
00:33:34,680 --> 00:33:36,480
That will seriously affect you.

697
00:33:36,480 --> 00:33:37,000
By then, this matter

698
00:33:37,000 --> 00:33:39,000
won't be something
that can simply be brushed aside.

699
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:40,160
I'm her teacher.

700
00:33:42,270 --> 00:33:43,290
No matter what,

701
00:33:44,240 --> 00:33:45,440
I'm older than she is.

702
00:33:45,620 --> 00:33:46,850
[Integrity in Character,
Diligence in Study]

703
00:33:47,250 --> 00:33:48,490
How about this?

704
00:33:49,240 --> 00:33:49,890
Lin,

705
00:33:50,270 --> 00:33:51,150
be careful with

706
00:33:51,240 --> 00:33:53,150
how you word the statement.

707
00:33:53,800 --> 00:33:57,060
[Integrity in Character,
Diligence in Study]

708
00:33:53,930 --> 00:33:56,000
Don't publish it on the school website.

709
00:33:56,000 --> 00:33:57,260
Just post it on campus.

710
00:33:57,510 --> 00:33:59,710
Keep the impact as minimal as possible.

711
00:33:59,830 --> 00:34:00,360
Alright.

712
00:34:03,440 --> 00:34:05,710
-Actually, Ms. Yan is quite kind.
-We must handle it well.

713
00:34:05,710 --> 00:34:06,900
Keep the impact to a minimum.

714
00:34:06,900 --> 00:34:09,030
Alright, don't worry, President Sun.

715
00:34:16,840 --> 00:34:17,370
Let's go.

716
00:34:17,920 --> 00:34:19,030
Let's go to the cafeteria together.

717
00:34:19,030 --> 00:34:19,699
My treat.

718
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:21,330
I packed my lunch today.

719
00:34:35,670 --> 00:34:38,110
Telling a mother who misses her son
to be patient

720
00:34:38,110 --> 00:34:41,040
is obviously
a completely meaningless suggestion.

721
00:34:41,190 --> 00:34:42,719
If you trust me and allow it,

722
00:34:43,070 --> 00:34:45,330
perhaps I could have a chat with your son.

723
00:34:57,230 --> 00:34:57,840
Goodbye.

724
00:34:59,350 --> 00:34:59,930
Jiale.

725
00:35:09,640 --> 00:35:10,150
Come on.

726
00:35:15,030 --> 00:35:17,540
I'm not here to force you
to come home with me.

727
00:35:18,190 --> 00:35:20,000
Your dad is working overtime today.

728
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:23,000
He asked me to take you
to my office to do your homework.

729
00:35:23,090 --> 00:35:24,310
I'll take you to his place later,

730
00:35:24,310 --> 00:35:24,800
okay?

731
00:35:28,360 --> 00:35:29,090
Here, let me.

732
00:35:42,540 --> 00:35:43,090
[Bulletin Board]

733
00:35:43,110 --> 00:35:45,560
[Notice on the Sudden Incident]

734
00:35:45,590 --> 00:35:46,890
[Involving Li, Class of 2015]

735
00:35:49,130 --> 00:35:50,720
[Homeroom Teacher Yan Ling is responsible
for the Level-2 teaching incident]

736
00:35:50,740 --> 00:35:52,560
[due to improper handling.]

737
00:35:55,970 --> 00:35:59,840
[Bulletin Board]

738
00:36:08,560 --> 00:36:09,260
Come in.

739
00:36:11,230 --> 00:36:11,790
Hello.

740
00:36:13,070 --> 00:36:14,930
I'm looking for Yan Ling, Ms. Yan.

741
00:36:15,300 --> 00:36:17,110
She went to tutor a student
on their thesis.

742
00:36:17,110 --> 00:36:18,240
She'll be back soon.

743
00:36:19,920 --> 00:36:20,610
Then...

744
00:36:21,360 --> 00:36:22,620
I'll wait for her here.

745
00:36:26,630 --> 00:36:28,920
You can grab a chair and have a seat.

746
00:36:29,590 --> 00:36:31,320
It's fine. I'll stand for a bit.

747
00:36:35,320 --> 00:36:36,600
May I ask

748
00:36:37,000 --> 00:36:37,800
who you are?

749
00:36:38,590 --> 00:36:39,630
I'm her son.

750
00:36:39,730 --> 00:36:40,860
My name is Yan Jiale.

751
00:36:42,320 --> 00:36:42,840
Hello.

752
00:36:43,590 --> 00:36:44,520
Nice to meet you.

753
00:36:45,150 --> 00:36:46,200
My name is Luo Liang.

754
00:36:46,200 --> 00:36:49,400
I'm the attending physician
for one of her sick students.

755
00:36:49,590 --> 00:36:50,680
Is her illness

756
00:36:50,800 --> 00:36:52,480
really my mom's fault?

757
00:36:55,880 --> 00:36:58,540
That involves
the patient's personal privacy.

758
00:36:58,550 --> 00:36:59,810
I can't disclose that.

759
00:36:59,990 --> 00:37:01,590
But I can assure you

760
00:37:02,000 --> 00:37:04,320
that your mom is an excellent teacher.

761
00:37:05,550 --> 00:37:07,550
If she's really such a good teacher,

762
00:37:07,590 --> 00:37:09,320
why would she be disciplined?

763
00:37:12,800 --> 00:37:13,760
So, how do you

764
00:37:14,240 --> 00:37:16,330
and your father

765
00:37:16,590 --> 00:37:17,670
see your mom?

766
00:37:18,560 --> 00:37:20,620
How my dad sees my mom doesn't matter.

767
00:37:21,110 --> 00:37:22,710
He already has a girlfriend.

768
00:37:26,100 --> 00:37:26,960
What about you?

769
00:37:27,320 --> 00:37:28,920
What do you think of your mom?

770
00:37:42,480 --> 00:37:43,920
Thank you, Dr. Luo.

771
00:37:45,590 --> 00:37:47,390
There's nothing to thank me for.

772
00:37:47,440 --> 00:37:49,000
I made a new friend today.

773
00:37:49,510 --> 00:37:51,110
It was great meeting you too.

774
00:37:51,970 --> 00:37:52,920
I've got some things at the hospital.

775
00:37:52,920 --> 00:37:53,920
I'll be going now.

776
00:37:54,710 --> 00:37:55,710
Bye-bye, Dr. Luo.

777
00:37:55,840 --> 00:37:56,370
Bye-bye.

778
00:37:57,150 --> 00:37:57,900
You two...

779
00:37:58,440 --> 00:37:59,700
take your time to talk.

780
00:38:06,070 --> 00:38:07,760
I'll take you to your father's place.

781
00:38:07,760 --> 00:38:08,620
Are you hungry?

782
00:38:08,840 --> 00:38:10,770
Do you want to eat something first?

783
00:38:12,480 --> 00:38:13,770
I want to go home.

784
00:38:19,710 --> 00:38:22,190
I mean, I want to go back to my own home.

785
00:38:33,550 --> 00:38:34,880
When did you learn this?

786
00:38:35,000 --> 00:38:35,860
Who taught you?

787
00:38:36,670 --> 00:38:37,880
My godmother taught me.

788
00:38:37,880 --> 00:38:40,110
So you and your godmother were very close.

789
00:38:40,110 --> 00:38:40,790
Yes.

790
00:38:43,150 --> 00:38:45,950
You said your godmother was gentler
than your mom.

791
00:38:46,920 --> 00:38:49,360
So, is this a drawing of you
and your godmother?

792
00:38:49,360 --> 00:38:51,020
I miss my godmother very much.

793
00:38:55,560 --> 00:38:56,680
Dealing with loss

794
00:38:57,230 --> 00:38:58,710
is a very difficult thing.

795
00:38:59,960 --> 00:39:02,960
Stealing a turtle, lying,
and running away from home—

796
00:39:03,440 --> 00:39:06,170
those things might seem serious
at first glance,

797
00:39:06,190 --> 00:39:07,000
but in truth,

798
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:09,520
they're just Jiale's stress responses

799
00:39:09,590 --> 00:39:11,390
to the pain of losing a loved one.

800
00:39:11,670 --> 00:39:13,400
My professor once told me this.

801
00:39:16,110 --> 00:39:18,040
Those who take their own lives are,

802
00:39:18,230 --> 00:39:19,830
in a way, placing their bones

803
00:39:20,550 --> 00:39:22,360
upon the hearts of the living.

804
00:39:24,070 --> 00:39:25,230
And that guilt,

805
00:39:25,960 --> 00:39:26,690
self-blame,

806
00:39:27,360 --> 00:39:28,160
and confusion

807
00:39:29,670 --> 00:39:30,840
weigh heavily on your heart

808
00:39:30,840 --> 00:39:33,300
for a long time
until you can barely breathe.

809
00:39:34,550 --> 00:39:35,610
That's true for you

810
00:39:36,630 --> 00:39:37,760
and for Jiale too.

811
00:39:42,510 --> 00:39:44,230
Set everything else aside for now.

812
00:39:44,230 --> 00:39:45,830
Focus on his feelings first.

813
00:39:46,920 --> 00:39:48,380
Before, there was Leilei.

814
00:39:49,070 --> 00:39:50,920
Now Jiale only has you.

815
00:40:07,490 --> 00:40:08,280
Don't fight.

816
00:40:10,150 --> 00:40:10,710
Let's go.

817
00:40:11,730 --> 00:40:12,930
-Bye-bye!
-Bye-bye.

818
00:40:16,510 --> 00:40:17,770
Be careful on the road!

819
00:40:30,590 --> 00:40:31,510
I'm sorry.

820
00:40:34,810 --> 00:40:37,780
Mom, I shouldn't have taken
Sun Haoyang's turtle.

821
00:40:40,600 --> 00:40:42,600
I'll give it back to him tomorrow.

822
00:40:45,760 --> 00:40:48,560
Actually, I did it not
just because I was mad at him.

823
00:40:48,960 --> 00:40:51,220
It's mainly because I saw him keep poking

824
00:40:51,230 --> 00:40:52,070
the turtle with his pencil

825
00:40:52,070 --> 00:40:53,670
and even jabbing at its eyes.

826
00:40:59,360 --> 00:41:00,320
Then we...

827
00:41:02,410 --> 00:41:03,810
won't give it back to him.

828
00:41:15,260 --> 00:41:17,300
Can we really set it free?

829
00:41:18,240 --> 00:41:20,300
Nothing is more important than life.

830
00:41:30,590 --> 00:41:31,110
Go on.

831
00:41:32,000 --> 00:41:34,010
Go find your friends.

832
00:41:39,710 --> 00:41:40,670
Thank you, Mom.

833
00:41:42,820 --> 00:41:45,440
I wish Godmother could release

834
00:41:45,440 --> 00:41:46,500
the turtle with us.

835
00:41:49,840 --> 00:41:54,480
[The Dark Romance]

836
00:41:56,960 --> 00:41:57,510
This way.

837
00:42:14,620 --> 00:42:20,490
[Yan Ling]

838
00:42:27,960 --> 00:42:28,910
See?

839
